<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#targetType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#textualRepresentation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#textualRepresentation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "textualRepresentation" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#textualRepresentation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Element: The TextualRepresentations that annotate this Element." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#textualRepresentation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#type> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "type" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#type> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Feature: Types that restrict the values of this Feature, such that the values must be instances of all the types. The types of a Feature are derived from its typings and the types of its subsettings. If the Feature is chained, then the types of the last Feature in the chain are also types of the chained Feature.\nFeatureTyping: The Type that is being applied by this FeatureTyping." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#type> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDifferenced> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDifferenced> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "typeDifferenced" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDifferenced> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Differencing: Type with interpretations partly determined by differencingType, as described in Type::differencingType." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDifferenced> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDisjoined> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDisjoined> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "typeDisjoined" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDisjoined> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Disjoining: Type asserted to be disjoint with the disjoiningType." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeDisjoined> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeIntersected> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeIntersected> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "typeIntersected" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeIntersected> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Intersecting: Type with interpretations partly determined by intersectingType, as described in Type::intersectingType." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeIntersected> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeUnioned> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeUnioned> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "typeUnioned" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeUnioned> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Unioning: Type with interpretations partly determined by unioningType, as described in Type::unioningType." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typeUnioned> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typedFeature> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typedFeature> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "typedFeature" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typedFeature> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "FeatureTyping: The Feature that has a type determined by this FeatureTyping." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#typedFeature> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "unioningType" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Type: The interpretations of a Type with unioningTypes are asserted to be the same as those of all the unioningTypes together, which are the Types derived from the unioningType of the ownedUnionings of this Type. For example, a Classifier for people might be the union of Classifiers for all the sexes. Similarly, a feature for people's children might be the union of features dividing them in the same ways as people in general.\nUnioning: Type that partly determines interpretations of typeUnioned, as described in Type::unioningType." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "upperBound" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MultiplicityRange: The Expression whose result is the upper bound of the MultiplicityRange." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#value> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#value> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "value" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#value> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "FeatureValue: The Expression that provides the value as a result.\nLiteralBoolean: The Boolean value that is the result of evaluating this LiteralBoolean.\nLiteralInteger: The Integer value that is the result of evaluating this LiteralInteger.\nLiteralString: The String value that is the result of evaluating this Expression.\nLiteralRational: The value whose rational approximation is the result of evaluating this LiteralRational." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#value> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#visibility> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#visibility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "visibility" .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#visibility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Membership: Whether or not the Membership of the memberElement in the membershipOwningNamespace is publicly visible outside that Namespace.\nImport: The visibility level of the imported members from this Import relative to the importOwningNamespace. The default is private." .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#visibility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#> .
